1
00:02:12,530 --> 00:02:15,330
Run for Young

2
00:02:19,510 --> 00:02:20,670
Luo Shenxi!

3
00:02:21,510 --> 00:02:23,070
Why are you acting so good?

4
00:02:23,670 --> 00:02:25,230
You won't hang out with your friends?

5
00:02:26,070 --> 00:02:26,830
I'm in the twelfth grade.

6
00:02:26,830 --> 00:02:28,270
I will definitely study hard.

7
00:02:28,510 --> 00:02:29,550
Seriously?

8
00:02:29,790 --> 00:02:30,910
How touching!

9
00:02:32,230 --> 00:02:33,670
Then forget about this.

10
00:02:37,950 --> 00:02:38,470
Mom.

11
00:02:39,510 --> 00:02:40,550
Is it possible?

12
00:02:41,070 --> 00:02:42,030
It is possible.

13
00:02:42,350 --> 00:02:43,190
Goody two-shoes.

14
00:02:43,950 --> 00:02:44,950
If you go out,

15
00:02:45,110 --> 00:02:46,110
just take care.

16
00:03:04,670 --> 00:03:07,870
At seven o'clock tonight,

17
00:03:09,510 --> 00:03:12,590
I'll see you at Jiefangbei.

18
00:03:14,090 --> 00:03:19,570
Sure.
See you there.
Let's all wear red scarf.

19
00:03:31,650 --> 00:03:36,250
Episode 6 When You Fall in Love, You Give Your All

20
00:03:56,990 --> 00:03:58,110
Who are you looking for?

21
00:03:58,430 --> 00:03:59,750
I've seen you here many times.

22
00:04:00,270 --> 00:04:01,910
I'm Liu Wenqin's classmate.

23
00:04:01,990 --> 00:04:02,950
I want to find him.

24
00:04:02,950 --> 00:04:04,550
They have moved.

25
00:04:04,670 --> 00:04:06,190
When did they move away?

26
00:04:06,510 --> 00:04:07,830
Mr. Liu is sick.

27
00:04:08,270 --> 00:04:09,470
Quite sick.

28
00:04:09,510 --> 00:04:10,990
He couldn't work in the city anymore.

29
00:04:11,110 --> 00:04:12,110
So they moved.

30
00:04:12,150 --> 00:04:14,110
Do you have their contact?

31
00:04:15,070 --> 00:04:15,670
No.

32
00:04:15,790 --> 00:04:17,030
What about Liu Wenqin?

33
00:04:17,910 --> 00:04:19,270
I feel so sorry for this kid.

34
00:04:20,750 --> 00:04:22,150
I don't know what he could do in the future.

35
00:04:50,230 --> 00:04:51,190
Anran, what a coincidence!

36
00:04:54,230 --> 00:04:54,910
By the way, Anran.

37
00:04:54,910 --> 00:04:55,950
My bro always wants to...

38
00:04:55,950 --> 00:04:57,150
Don't mention it. It's over.

39
00:04:57,870 --> 00:04:58,710
Tu Jun.

40
00:04:59,350 --> 00:05:00,910
I am applying to study in the UK.

41
00:05:01,550 --> 00:05:03,110
I may leave without taking the NCEE.

42
00:05:04,710 --> 00:05:05,230
UK?

43
00:05:07,110 --> 00:05:08,110
Isn't that far away?

44
00:05:09,350 --> 00:05:10,190
Yeah.

45
00:05:10,910 --> 00:05:12,550
It takes more than ten hours by plane.

46
00:05:16,230 --> 00:05:17,310
More than ten hours.

47
00:05:18,270 --> 00:05:19,350
It's really a little far away.

48
00:05:22,470 --> 00:05:23,150
It's better that way.

49
00:05:23,870 --> 00:05:26,190
So that I can forget those unhappy memories.

50
00:05:28,150 --> 00:05:28,430
By the way!

51
00:05:28,430 --> 00:05:29,550
It's going to be very lively tonight.

52
00:05:29,550 --> 00:05:30,190
Do you want to...

53
00:05:38,230 --> 00:05:39,510
Did you give her the necklace

54
00:05:39,630 --> 00:05:40,230
you bought?

55
00:05:41,350 --> 00:05:41,790
No.

56
00:05:41,910 --> 00:05:42,670
Why not?

57
00:05:44,830 --> 00:05:47,150
I've tried so hard to buy it.

58
00:05:48,790 --> 00:05:50,870
But it was just the fifth prize in the restaurant.

59
00:05:51,510 --> 00:05:52,350
But

60
00:05:53,310 --> 00:05:55,310
what you bought is different from theirs.

61
00:05:56,190 --> 00:05:57,070
What's the difference?

62
00:05:57,070 --> 00:05:58,190
It's with your feelings.

63
00:06:05,910 --> 00:06:06,910
What's the matter?

64
00:06:07,190 --> 00:06:08,190
I'm so scared.

65
00:06:08,910 --> 00:06:09,870
Why?

66
00:06:23,950 --> 00:06:25,190
Because I don't know

67
00:06:25,190 --> 00:06:26,870
what he's going to do.

68
00:06:30,350 --> 00:06:30,950
Director Pan.

69
00:06:32,470 --> 00:06:32,990
Dajun.

70
00:06:33,430 --> 00:06:33,950
What's the matter?

71
00:06:36,750 --> 00:06:38,150
Those kids have been

72
00:06:38,750 --> 00:06:39,790
well-behaved recently.

73
00:06:40,430 --> 00:06:40,910
So?

74
00:06:41,990 --> 00:06:42,830
I think

75
00:06:42,830 --> 00:06:44,510
I can regroup

76
00:06:44,590 --> 00:06:45,830
my marathon team again, right?

77
00:06:46,190 --> 00:06:46,670
Forget it.

78
00:06:46,750 --> 00:06:48,390
School can complete the task through other recreational

79
00:06:48,590 --> 00:06:49,350
and sports activities.

80
00:06:51,470 --> 00:06:54,110
For me, it's not just about

81
00:06:54,110 --> 00:06:55,270
completing tasks.

82
00:06:55,430 --> 00:06:56,990
But it's the same for the school.

83
00:06:57,750 --> 00:06:58,750
Besides,

84
00:06:58,790 --> 00:07:00,510
a leopard can't change its nature.

85
00:07:00,750 --> 00:07:01,590
Those kids

86
00:07:01,630 --> 00:07:02,630
won't be really well-behaved.

87
00:07:03,150 --> 00:07:04,270
So, it's impossible!

88
00:07:05,710 --> 00:07:06,510
Director Pan.

89
00:07:07,990 --> 00:07:08,830
Director Pan!

90
00:07:09,430 --> 00:07:10,870
They are just kids.

91
00:07:11,630 --> 00:07:12,470
Moreover,

92
00:07:14,390 --> 00:07:15,550
nothing is impossible

93
00:07:15,550 --> 00:07:17,390
in this world.

94
00:07:18,350 --> 00:07:20,750
For example, the radio stations have been saying

95
00:07:20,750 --> 00:07:22,350
that it hasn't snowed in Chongqing for years.

96
00:07:22,790 --> 00:07:24,910
It's impossible for the main city of Chongqing

97
00:07:24,910 --> 00:07:26,030
to snow.

98
00:07:31,430 --> 00:07:33,310
How do you know it's impossible?

99
00:07:34,470 --> 00:07:35,670
Yuanyuan.

100
00:07:35,910 --> 00:07:37,990
I heard it snowed everywhere this year.

101
00:07:38,030 --> 00:07:40,870
It's snowing in Guangzhou and Chengdu.

102
00:07:41,030 --> 00:07:42,110
How is that possible?

103
00:07:42,470 --> 00:07:44,030
Snow in Chongqing?

104
00:07:44,110 --> 00:07:45,270
Unless there is a miracle!

105
00:07:47,830 --> 00:07:48,310
What are those?

106
00:07:48,750 --> 00:07:49,750
What else could they be?

107
00:07:49,750 --> 00:07:50,670
There are some fools at the door

108
00:07:50,670 --> 00:07:51,550
begging me to bring them in.

109
00:07:53,310 --> 00:07:54,230
Those are for you.

110
00:07:54,750 --> 00:07:55,550
You're trying to play cool.

111
00:07:55,590 --> 00:07:56,390
Look now.

112
00:07:56,670 --> 00:07:58,750
I can't believe girls give you greeting cards.

113
00:07:59,150 --> 00:07:59,670
I don't want them.

114
00:08:02,190 --> 00:08:03,790
I'm not your postman!

115
00:08:04,150 --> 00:08:05,310
There is no such service!

116
00:08:05,670 --> 00:08:07,030
Send them back yourself!

117
00:08:08,590 --> 00:08:10,110
The fool from Class 4 gave it to you.

118
00:08:10,470 --> 00:08:11,070
Let me take a look.

119
00:08:11,070 --> 00:08:12,470
Give it back. I haven't read it yet!

120
00:08:12,470 --> 00:08:14,230
The fool from Class 3 gave it to you.

121
00:08:14,390 --> 00:08:14,990
Thank you.

122
00:08:15,150 --> 00:08:16,030
Oh, nice.

123
00:08:16,270 --> 00:08:16,870
I have one, too.

124
00:08:16,870 --> 00:08:17,350
This is yours.

125
00:08:17,550 --> 00:08:19,230
That handwriting is really nice.

126
00:08:21,750 --> 00:08:22,630
Who gave it to you?

127
00:08:23,110 --> 00:08:24,670
Who else could it be?

128
00:08:36,510 --> 00:08:37,390
What are you looking at?

129
00:08:39,870 --> 00:08:41,230
Why not open it and have a look?

130
00:08:42,870 --> 00:08:44,350
These greeting cards are very cheesy.

131
00:08:45,150 --> 00:08:46,990
It has nothing to do with me.

132
00:08:46,990 --> 00:08:48,430
I don't care about these cards.

133
00:08:49,990 --> 00:08:50,630
Ma Tian.

134
00:08:54,710 --> 00:08:56,150
It's a holiday today.

135
00:08:56,190 --> 00:08:57,350
Are you available tonight?

136
00:08:57,990 --> 00:08:58,830
I'm busy tonight.

137
00:08:58,830 --> 00:08:59,710
I want to review my lessons.

138
00:09:00,630 --> 00:09:02,110
Then can I study with you?

139
00:09:03,150 --> 00:09:04,230
Your grades are so good.

140
00:09:04,310 --> 00:09:05,630
You don't have to review with me, do you?

141
00:09:09,110 --> 00:09:09,510
Come on.

142
00:09:09,990 --> 00:09:11,030
Review yesterday's lessons with me.

143
00:09:13,230 --> 00:09:15,110
Indeed, you only help the underachieving students.

144
00:09:18,470 --> 00:09:19,430
OK, Ma Tian.

145
00:09:19,430 --> 00:09:20,630
Let's review together!

146
00:09:26,270 --> 00:09:28,230
How could you be so indifferent?

147
00:09:29,350 --> 00:09:31,270
I'm only kind to strong girls

148
00:09:31,550 --> 00:09:32,590
as I'm afraid of being beaten by you.

149
00:09:39,350 --> 00:09:40,950
You teenagers

150
00:09:41,710 --> 00:09:43,390
like to follow the trend and celebrate western festivals.

151
00:09:44,430 --> 00:09:45,350
Chinese people

152
00:09:45,630 --> 00:09:47,550
should celebrate our own festivals.

153
00:09:47,870 --> 00:09:48,350
Don't waste time

154
00:09:48,350 --> 00:09:49,950
on these things anymore.

155
00:09:51,310 --> 00:09:52,190
Take out the book.

156
00:09:54,390 --> 00:09:55,270
Tu Jun!

157
00:09:56,630 --> 00:09:58,230
Why are you in such a hurry?

158
00:09:58,990 --> 00:10:00,550
Anran, it's a festive night today,

159
00:10:00,670 --> 00:10:01,790
I have a special surprise for you.

160
00:10:02,310 --> 00:10:03,510
What surprise?

161
00:10:03,630 --> 00:10:04,230
Don't worry.

162
00:10:04,230 --> 00:10:05,310
I won't let you down.

163
00:10:11,030 --> 00:10:11,830
Where's Doggo?

164
00:10:13,310 --> 00:10:13,950
I don't know.

165
00:10:15,830 --> 00:10:17,750
That brat is always noisy.

166
00:10:17,750 --> 00:10:18,510
He is not around today,

167
00:10:18,550 --> 00:10:19,870
I'm actually not used to it.

168
00:10:22,190 --> 00:10:23,590
Where shall we have fun tonight?

169
00:10:27,870 --> 00:10:28,950
I have an appointment tonight.

170
00:10:29,670 --> 00:10:30,710
I can't hang out with you.

171
00:10:32,470 --> 00:10:33,310
I'm busy, too.

172
00:10:40,230 --> 00:10:41,150
Forget it.

173
00:10:41,750 --> 00:10:43,270
You're both grown up.

174
00:10:44,470 --> 00:10:46,470
Not the partners you used to be.

175
00:10:48,150 --> 00:10:49,670
Let me die alone.

176
00:10:52,230 --> 00:10:54,310
I invited Yuanyuan to go skating in Metropolis tonight.

177
00:10:54,590 --> 00:10:55,270
Are you going?

178
00:10:55,470 --> 00:10:56,390
I will pass.

179
00:10:58,190 --> 00:10:59,030
Jiao.

180
00:10:59,390 --> 00:11:01,470
Did you get a greeting card today?

181
00:11:02,990 --> 00:11:05,150
I don't like this western stuff.

182
00:11:05,190 --> 00:11:06,830
You all know that.

183
00:11:07,710 --> 00:11:09,270
I don't like it, either.

184
00:11:09,550 --> 00:11:10,310
But,

185
00:11:10,310 --> 00:11:12,630
I received a lot of greeting cards today.

186
00:11:12,750 --> 00:11:15,190
I don't even know where to put them.

187
00:11:15,350 --> 00:11:15,990
Let's go.

188
00:11:15,990 --> 00:11:16,750
So annoying.

189
00:11:17,430 --> 00:11:18,270
Then burn them.

190
00:11:23,350 --> 00:11:24,270
Oh, Ding Rongliang.

191
00:11:24,990 --> 00:11:27,710
That card you sent me today is very beautiful.

192
00:11:27,710 --> 00:11:28,670
I like it very much.

193
00:11:28,670 --> 00:11:29,590
Thank you.

194
00:11:29,950 --> 00:11:31,350
You're welcome.

195
00:11:35,950 --> 00:11:36,510
What?

196
00:11:39,430 --> 00:11:40,630
What's the matter?

197
00:11:50,070 --> 00:11:50,670
What?

198
00:11:53,390 --> 00:11:54,550
This one looks good, too.

199
00:11:54,670 --> 00:11:55,630
I'll take this one.

200
00:11:55,630 --> 00:11:57,270
No. Don't you rob me again!

201
00:11:57,270 --> 00:11:57,910
This one looks good.

202
00:11:59,110 --> 00:11:59,630
OK.

203
00:12:00,430 --> 00:12:01,590
Which do you want?

204
00:12:01,710 --> 00:12:02,710
I won't give it to you. Only one left.

205
00:12:02,710 --> 00:12:03,950
Gift that.

206
00:12:04,110 --> 00:12:04,470
For whom?

207
00:12:04,470 --> 00:12:04,990
Looks so good.

208
00:12:07,350 --> 00:12:08,790
Why do you like him?

209
00:12:10,710 --> 00:12:11,950
Why do you like him?

210
00:12:11,950 --> 00:12:12,990
I just like him.

211
00:12:20,310 --> 00:12:20,950
So early?

212
00:12:21,310 --> 00:12:21,790
Morning.

213
00:12:21,790 --> 00:12:22,710
Morning.

214
00:13:25,510 --> 00:13:26,030
Uncle.

215
00:13:29,150 --> 00:13:29,830
Jun.

216
00:13:32,070 --> 00:13:33,230
Uncle, did you eat?

217
00:13:34,150 --> 00:13:34,790
No.

218
00:13:39,390 --> 00:13:40,550
Uncle. Let's eat.

219
00:13:50,230 --> 00:13:50,950
Jun.

220
00:13:52,590 --> 00:13:53,790
Every time you come here,

221
00:13:54,030 --> 00:13:56,110
you come to cook a bowl of noodles for me, right?

222
00:13:57,110 --> 00:13:57,790
I come to see you.

223
00:14:09,110 --> 00:14:11,310
Wenqin has been very good since childhood.

224
00:14:14,510 --> 00:14:17,590
I didn't expect such a thing to happen.

225
00:14:20,670 --> 00:14:21,350
Do you think

226
00:14:22,990 --> 00:14:24,590
I'm so useless

227
00:14:25,510 --> 00:14:27,350
that he had to earn money earlier?

228
00:14:30,470 --> 00:14:30,990
No.

229
00:14:33,830 --> 00:14:34,790
Why then?

230
00:14:39,950 --> 00:14:41,110
Maybe

231
00:14:43,430 --> 00:14:45,470
everyone grows up differently.

232
00:14:52,430 --> 00:14:53,310
Jun.

233
00:14:54,630 --> 00:14:55,310
In contrast,

234
00:14:57,390 --> 00:14:58,510
I felt anxious every day

235
00:14:59,990 --> 00:15:01,190
when he wasn't around.

236
00:15:03,470 --> 00:15:04,750
But now,

237
00:15:05,790 --> 00:15:07,070
I feel at ease.

238
00:15:08,630 --> 00:15:09,670
At least I know

239
00:15:10,230 --> 00:15:11,230
where he is

240
00:15:11,790 --> 00:15:12,790
and he's safe.

241
00:15:14,350 --> 00:15:15,230
I'm sorry, uncle.

242
00:15:19,310 --> 00:15:20,550
What are you sorry for?

243
00:15:24,190 --> 00:15:25,150
I should have

244
00:15:27,150 --> 00:15:28,270
stopped him from doing those.

245
00:15:53,390 --> 00:15:53,910
Dude.

246
00:15:53,950 --> 00:15:56,110
Isn't it a little crazy?

247
00:15:56,310 --> 00:15:57,870
You drive then!

248
00:15:57,870 --> 00:15:58,910
I won't drive.

249
00:15:59,310 --> 00:16:00,950
Then don't even speak!

250
00:16:01,390 --> 00:16:03,070
You're affecting me.

251
00:16:03,110 --> 00:16:04,750
I rarely drive 70 miles per hour.

252
00:16:05,430 --> 00:16:06,990
I feel so free!

253
00:16:07,150 --> 00:16:08,630
Yet you're still not satisfied!

254
00:16:10,110 --> 00:16:10,950
Dude.

255
00:16:10,950 --> 00:16:12,310
Do you have another helmet for me?

256
00:16:12,350 --> 00:16:13,670
Give me one, please.

257
00:16:13,670 --> 00:16:14,870
You're here to enjoy the wind!

258
00:16:15,310 --> 00:16:16,550
Why do you need a helmet?

259
00:16:17,550 --> 00:16:18,870
You don't even have a helmet for me!

260
00:16:18,870 --> 00:16:20,590
How can you drive motorcycle taxi!

261
00:16:20,750 --> 00:16:21,750
You can get off.

262
00:16:21,750 --> 00:16:22,510
No way!

263
00:16:24,350 --> 00:16:25,150
Then,

264
00:16:25,190 --> 00:16:25,790
just shut up!

265
00:16:39,030 --> 00:16:39,710
Jiao.

266
00:16:39,710 --> 00:16:40,950
It's only been a noon,

267
00:16:40,950 --> 00:16:42,110
and you got so many cards.

268
00:16:46,070 --> 00:16:47,510
It's profound accumulation.

269
00:16:48,070 --> 00:16:49,830
What's written in those greeting cards?

270
00:16:52,670 --> 00:16:54,230
I haven't had time to read them yet.

271
00:17:13,630 --> 00:17:14,310
What?

272
00:17:15,230 --> 00:17:17,470
Why are your greeting cards all blank, Jiao?

273
00:17:17,750 --> 00:17:19,070
What are you doing?

274
00:17:21,790 --> 00:17:22,590
You two!

275
00:17:22,590 --> 00:17:24,470
You two idiots, what are you doing!

276
00:17:24,750 --> 00:17:25,830
Sorry, Jiao.

277
00:17:27,590 --> 00:17:29,870
Who would send blank greeting cards?

278
00:17:32,550 --> 00:17:33,550
So what!

279
00:17:39,190 --> 00:17:41,230
I think you bought them yourself!

280
00:17:42,630 --> 00:17:44,190
Bought greeting cards for herself.

281
00:17:46,270 --> 00:17:48,030
Bought greeting cards for herself.

282
00:17:56,350 --> 00:17:57,630
Why are the greeting cards

283
00:17:57,630 --> 00:17:59,310
I bought today here?

284
00:17:59,630 --> 00:18:00,870
I think I put them in the wrong drawer.

285
00:18:06,110 --> 00:18:07,350
That's even worse.

286
00:18:07,550 --> 00:18:09,670
No one sent you a greeting card.

287
00:18:10,150 --> 00:18:11,030
But,

288
00:18:11,030 --> 00:18:13,350
I only received 38 greeting cards.

289
00:18:13,390 --> 00:18:14,270
That's all.

290
00:18:23,790 --> 00:18:24,670
Maybe you will

291
00:18:24,750 --> 00:18:26,150
get a lot of greeting cards tomorrow.

292
00:18:28,150 --> 00:18:29,150
Forget it.

293
00:18:29,830 --> 00:18:31,350
It's so humiliating.

